Uses of Package
xxl.core.indexStructures

  • Packages that use xxl.core.indexStructures 
    Package Description
    xxl.core.indexStructures
    Provides important index structures like B-trees, R-trees, M-trees and bulk-loading-algorithms.
    xxl.core.indexStructures.builder
    Providing builder classes for various index structures.
    xxl.core.indexStructures.builder.BPlusTree
    The builder class for BPlusTrees.
    xxl.core.indexStructures.keyRanges  
    xxl.core.indexStructures.rtrees  
    xxl.core.indexStructures.separators  
    xxl.core.indexStructures.vLengthBPlusTree
    Experimental Package for variable length B+tree implementation.
    xxl.core.spatial
    Support data types and building-blocks for spatial, temporal and mining algorithms (e.g. similarity joins)
    xxl.core.spatial.cursors
    Provides mappers for different type of Point and Rectangle objects as well as several join algorithms: nested loops distance similarity-join for Points, the spatial join algorithm based on space-filling curves proposed by Jack Orenstein, similarity-join algorithm "GESS: Generic External Space Sweep" and hash-based plane sweep for two-dimensional data.
    xxl.core.spatial.geometries.cursors
    A collection of spatial queries.
    xxl.core.spatial.histograms.utils  
    xxl.core.spatial.predicates
    Useful spatial predicates such as Contains, Overlap, Within (Euclidean distance), etc .
    xxl.core.spatial.rectangles
    Implemetns the base type Rectangle for high-dimensional rectangle objects (hyper-cubes) and extentions for different coordinate types (double, float, long).
    xxl.core.spatial.spatialBPlusTree  
    xxl.core.spatial.spatialBPlusTree.cursors  
    xxl.core.util
    This package provides miscellaneous utility classes that don't belong strictly to an other xxl-package.
  • Classes in xxl.core.indexStructures used by xxl.core.indexStructures 
    Class and Description
    AutoDeleteMVBTree.LeafInfo
    Contains information about one leaf node of the MVBTree.
    AutoDeleteMVBTree.NotifyHeap
    This class extends the DynamicHeap by providing a mechanism to notify a listener whenever an object in the heap changes its position.
    BPlusIndexedSet
    An implementation of the IndexedSet super class to use sets which are indexed by a BPlusTree.
    BPlusTree
    This class implements a B+Tree.
    BPlusTree.IndexEntry
    This class describes the index entries of the BPlusTree (i.e.
    BPlusTree.KeyRange
    This class represents key ranges (i.e. intervals of keys).
    BPlusTree.Node
    This class is used to represent leaf- and non-leaf nodes of a BPlusTree.
    BPlusTree.Node.MergeInfo
    A MergeInfo contains information about a merge (or redistribution).
    BPlusTree.Node.SplitInfo
    A SplitInfo contains information about a split.
    BPlusTree.NodeConverter
    A NodeConverter is used by the BPlusTree to convert the Nodes for I/O-purposes.
    BPlusTreeBulkLoading
    This class provides functionality to bulk-load a BPlusTree.
    BTree
    This class implements a B+Tree based index.
    BTree.Node
    Node is the class used to represent leaf- and non-leaf nodes of BTree.
    Descriptor
    A descriptor describes the region represented by a given subtree.
    Entry.WithKey
    Querying data from a IndexedSet is done by queries over the keys.
    FixedQuery
    A subclass of AbstractView is a fixed non-editable portion of data of a IndexedSet.
    HilbertRTree
    HilbertRTree with R*tree split(1-2 split policy) and BPlusTree merge strategies.
    HilbertRTree.NodeConverter 
    HilbertRTree.ORKeyRange 
    HilbertRTree.ORSeparator
    Extends Separator with Rectangle field which represents the MBR.
    IndexedSet
    The abstract base class IndexedSet is a Java SortedSet implementation to wrap the abilities of various index structures in order to act like a normal Java SortedSet.
    MTree
    An ORTree for objects with spheres as regions.
    MTree.Node
    Node is the class used to represent leaf- and non-leaf nodes of MTree.
    MultiDiskBTree
    This class implements a BTree which stores its leaf-nodes on multiple disks.
    MVBT
    MVBTree wiht new node layout
    MVBT.Node
    The experimantal layout: for index nodes we manage two lists first list stores live entries second list stores deleted entries this allows to run chooseSubTree method in O(log B) instead of O(B) and we have only 4 bytes space overhead
    MVBT.NodeConverter
    This Converter is concerned with serializing of nodes to write or read them into or from the external storage.
    MVBTPlus
    This class implements a MVBTPlus bulk-loading algorithm; see D.
    MVBTPlus.Element
    Data entry wrapper.
    MVBTPlus.IndexEntry
    This class extends BPlusTree.IndexEntry.
    MVBTPlus.LoadState
    Current bulk-loading state used internally to mark the current processing step
    MVBTPlus.LongVersion
    Version wrapper.
    MVBTPlus.Node
    This is a MVBT node implementation.
    MVBTPlus.NodeConverter
    Converter for MVBTPlus Nodes.
    MVBTPlus.OperationType
    Type of operation decoded in MVBTPlus.Element.
    MVBTPlus.ReorgInfo
    SplitInfo: contains necessary information for conducting a node reorganization operation
    MVBTPlus.SplitTocken
    This tokens are used for decoding reorganization type
    MVBTPlus.StackInfoObject
    This class implements a tuple.
    MVBTree
    This Class is an implementation of MVBT index structure "An asymptotically optimal multiversion B-tree" Becker Bruno, Gschwind Stephan, Ohler Thomas, Seeger Bernhard and Widmayer, Peter VLDB 1996
    MVBTree.BlockDelInfo
    Contains information about one block of the MVBTree, i.e. the block's ID in the underlying container and the block's deletion version.
    MVBTree.LeafEntry
    This class represents the entries which can be stored in the leaves of the MVBTree.
    MVBTree.Lifespan
    Objects of this class are version intervals and represent life spans of the entries sotred in the MVBTree.
    MVBTree.MVRegion 
    MVBTree.MVSeparator 
    MVBTree.Node
    This class represents the Nodes of the MVBTree.
    MVBTree.Node.SplitInfo 
    MVBTree.Version
    This is an interface for version instances used by the MVBTree.
    ORTree
    The class ORTree (Overlapping Region Tree) is a generic and highly flexible super-class that implements features used by grow- and post-trees which stores objects with descriptors which may overlap.
    ORTree.IndexEntry
    This class describes the index entries (i.e. the entries of the non-leaf nodes) of a tree.
    ORTree.IndexEntryConverter
    The instances of this class are converters to write index entries to the external storage (or any other DataOutput) or read them from it (or any other DataInput).
    ORTree.Node
    Node is the class used to represent leaf- and non-leaf nodes of ORTree.
    ORTree.Node.SplitInfo
    SplitInfo contains information about a split.
    ORTree.NodeConverter
    The instances of this class are converters to write nodes to the external storage (or any other DataOutput) or read them from it (or any other DataInput).
    QueryCursor
    This class represents lazy Cursors which can be used to perform queries on a Tree.
    RevisedRTree.Node
    Node is the class used to represent leaf- and non-leaf nodes of RTree.
    RevisedRTree.Node.Distribution
    Distribution is the class used to represent the distribution of entries of a node of the RTree into two partitions used for a split.
    RTree
    An ORTree for objects with bounding rectangles as regions.
    RTree.Node
    Node is the class used to represent leaf- and non-leaf nodes of RTree.
    RTree.Node.Distribution
    Distribution is the class used to represent the distribution of entries of a node of the RTree into two partitions used for a split.
    RTree.Node.SplitInfo
    SplitInfo contains information about a split.
    Separator
    This class describes the known separtors of the B+ tree.
    Sphere
    This class implements a Descriptor that is a sphere.
    Sphere.SphereCenterDistance
    A class for computing the distance between the centers of Spheres.
    Sphere.SphereMinimumDistance
    A class for computing the minimum distance between Spheres.
    Tree
    The Tree-class is a generic and highly flexible super-class that implements features used by grow- and post-trees.
    Tree.IndexEntry
    This class describes the index entries (i.e. the entries of the non-leaf nodes) of a tree.
    Tree.Node
    Node is the class used to represent leaf- and non-leaf nodes.
    Tree.Node.SplitInfo
    SplitInfo contains information about a split.
    Tree.Query
    Queries on the Tree are evaluated lazily (ONC).
    Tree.Query.Candidate
    A Candidate is an entry of the priority queue used for queries.
    XTree
    The XTree is a variant of the RTree for high dimensional data which avoids splits which would result in high overlap.
    XTree.IndexEntry
    This class describes the index entries (i.e. the entries of the non-leaf nodes) of a x-tree.
    XTree.Node
    Node is the class used to represent leaf- and non-leaf nodes of XTree.
    XTree.Node.SplitInfo
    SplitInfo contains information about a split.
